The 
Trachelidae Simon, 1897
is a small to medium-sized spider family that is currently represented by 282 species belonging to 23 genera, with a worldwide distribution. Of these, only six genera and 35 known species have been recorded from 
China
(

; 

). Since the start of the 21st century, taxonomic research on this group has been gradually increasing, mostly focused on Asia and the Afrotropical Region, especially in the last decade (e.g., 

; 

, 

